<h1>Manage Custom Fields for Opportunity in Salesforce</h1>
<ol>
	<li>Go to the Sales force site. For Developer account, e.g. <a href="https://ap2.salesforce.com" target="_blank">https://ap2.salesforce.com</a></li>
	<li>Login with your autorized Account of Salesforce.</li>
	<li>Then Click on the “Setup” menu.</li>
	<li>In this you see the “Build” Panel & select the “Customize” option.</li>
	<li>Then click on the “Opportunity” Option & select the “Field” Label.</li>
	<li>For creating a new Field click on “New” button at below side.</li>
	<li>Then select the Field’s Data type as Pick List and click “Next”</li>
	<li>Fill up the Details about Field and click “Next”. Provide values accordingly.</li>
	<li>Save the Field.</li>
	<li>So, New created field displayed in your view.</li>
	<li>Create one more field with above steps with different values.</li>
</ol>
